text: Yuliya Karol (born June 26, 1991) is a Belarusian middle-distance runner. She competed at the 2016 Summer Olympics in the women's 800 metres; her time of 2:01.09 in the heats did not qualify her for the semifinals. ==References== Category:1991 births Category:Living people Category:Belarusian female middle- distance runners Category:Olympic athletes of Belarus Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 2016 Summer Olympics
